results.deck: Black Label Games was the short-lived rebranding of Universal Interactive before the company would later rename itself "Vivendi-Universal Games." They have since merged with Activision to form Activision-Blizzard.
results.description:
They worked on three games: The Thing, Kill Bill, Metallica: The Game

The Thing was the only one that was released.
